    "body": "Problem: #38169 used compl_used_match to determine the CompleteDone reason, but this fires too broadly, it also changes the reason to \"accept\" when the popup was shown and the user dismissed it with <Esc> or <Space>, breaking snippet completion with autocomplete.\r\n\r\nSolution: Instead of checking compl_used_match in, check whether the pum was never shown (compl_match_array == NULL) in ins_compl_stop(). When a match was inserted but the pum never displayed, set the completed word so CompleteDone fires with reason \"accept\". This keeps the \"discard\" reason intact when the user dismisses a visible pum without confirming.\r\n\r\ncc @gravndal\r\n\r\nFix #38160\r\n",
    "closed_at": "2026-03-13T10:13:58Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "_links": {
                "html": {
                    "href": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/38280#discussion_r2932215184"
                },
                "pull_request": {
                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/pulls/38280"
                },
                "self": {
                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/pulls/comments/2932215184"
                }
            },
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "This isn't actually true, though the exact behaviour for some types of ins completion can depend on (at least) if `cot+=longest` is set.\n\nE.g. try:\n\n```\n$ nvim --clean\nihello world<CR><C-X><C-L><C-E>\n```\n\nNotice that you're still in complete mode and can cancel (or accept) the completion after doing `<C-X><C-L>`.\n\nSetting `cot+=longest` here would make it so the text remains in the buffer when cancelling, though this might just be a bug, I'm not too sure.\n\n---\n\nAnyway, I tested this and it works fine. Cancelling is still possible, and as there's nothing to indicate if something's a snippet, etc, this feature makes sense.\n\nThough, would it be possible to make this configurable with a completeopt like `cot+=acceptsinglematch` or something like that?",
            "commit_id": "4c22cd5b2eb1c4ccad3bb9a97814c8e578c6392f",
            "created_at": "2026-03-13T16:03:28Z",
            "diff_hunk": "@@ -2646,6 +2646,16 @@ static bool ins_compl_stop(const int c, const int prev_mode, bool retval)\n     redrawWinline(curwin, curwin->w_cursor.lnum);\n   }\n \n+  // When a match was inserted but the pum was never displayed\n+  // (eg: only one match with 'completeopt' \"menu\" without \"menuone\"),\n+  // the user had no opportunity to explicitly accept or dismiss it,",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/38280#discussion_r2932215184",
