            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> Setting cot+=longest here would make it so the text remains in the buffer when cancelling, though this might just be a bug, I'm not too sure.\r\n \r\n This behavior also exists in Vim. When `longest` is active, `compl_leader` gets set to the first completion item `(test)` in `ins_compl_longest_match`. As a result, after deleting and restoring the text, the value remains `test` 😮‍💨 It looks like a bug. I’ll try submitting a pr to vim later.",
            "commit_id": "4c22cd5b2eb1c4ccad3bb9a97814c8e578c6392f",
